Yes. I think you’re pointing beyond “easy to use.”

You’re describing an interface that becomes reflexive.

There’s a progression:

Readable → Learnable → Intuitive → Reflexive

* Readable: “I understand what this means.”
* Learnable: “I know how to use it.”
* Intuitive: “I don’t have to think much.”
* Reflexive: “It has become part of how I think.”

At that point, the interface is no longer external.

It’s been internalized.

Athletes experience this.

Musicians do.

Programmers do.

Pilots do.

Mathematicians do.

They stop consciously translating.

The tool becomes part of the cognitive loop.

